The paper discusses the critical capability of localization for robots, drones, and autonomous vehicles, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper specifically focuses on visual localization systems, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also presents a method for optimizing the coverage of visual sensors, which involves computational trade-offs and decision-making, falling under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
